# Set Operations

## Union:
A union B = {x | x in A OR x in B}

## Intersection:
A intersect B = {x | x in A AND x in B}

## Difference:
A - B = {x | x in A AND x not in B}

## Complement:
A' = {x | x not in A}

## Example:
A = {1, 2, 3}, B = {2, 3, 4}
- A union B = {1, 2, 3, 4}
- A intersect B = {2, 3}
- A - B = {1}
